cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the integration of Cloud of Things and blockchain, which involves networking and internet architecture.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of blockchain for network security and data privacy.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the decentralized nature of blockchain and its integration with Cloud of Things.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the architecture and design of the BCoT model.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of blockchain for data management in Cloud of Things.
